\date{2025-01-09}
\title{Validity of Probability Density Functions}
\taxon{theorem}

\p{
  The [PDF](ShanghaiTech-SI140A-0004) of a continuous r.v. #{X} must satisfy the following conditions:
  \ul{
    \li{\strong{Non-negativity}: #{f_X(x) \geq 0} for all #{x}.}
    \li{\strong{Normalization}: #{\int_{-\infty}^\infty f_X(x) \; \mathrm{d}x = 1}.}
  }
}